cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper discusses techniques to merge prototype-based vector quantization methods with neural networks, particularly for classification tasks and convolution operations. This makes it likely to fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), neural networks (cs.NE), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and natural language processing (cs.CL). However, since the focus is on classification and convolution, the first three categories are more likely than the last two.
